WEBVTT

00:01.218 --> 00:03.481
PREVIOUSLY ON "WHITE COLLAR"...

00:03.568 --> 00:06.354
TO OUR BEST
AND FINALSCORE.

00:06.441 --> 00:07.572
YOU ALMOST KILLED ME,
MOZZIE.

00:07.659 --> 00:08.965
WHAT DO YOU WANT,
KELLER?

00:09.052 --> 00:10.706
THIS IS YOUR LAST CHANCE
TO CUT ME IN ON YOUR TREASURE.

00:10.793 --> 00:12.099
REMEMBER,
I DID ASK NICELY.

00:12.186 --> 00:13.883
NOW I'M GONNA HAVE TO MAKE YOU
GIVE ME WHAT I WANT.

00:13.970 --> 00:15.885
Mozzie: NEAL, IT'S TIME FOR YOU
TO MAKE A CHOICE.

00:15.972 --> 00:17.017
DO YOU WANT TO LEAVE?

00:17.104 --> 00:18.279
NO.

00:18.366 --> 00:19.845
YOU'RE FOOLING YOURSELF

00:19.932 --> 00:22.239
IF YOU THINK THIS IS
WHO YOU REALLY ARE.

00:22.326 --> 00:23.284
I'VE SEEN THE TREASURE.

00:23.371 --> 00:24.676
Yeah,
your boy Caffrey's got it.

00:24.763 --> 00:26.287
AND YOU WANT IT.

00:26.374 --> 00:27.462
YOU GONNA HELP ME
OR WHAT?

00:27.549 --> 00:28.724
WHY WOULD I HELP YOU?

00:28.811 --> 00:30.769
HOW ABOUT YOU GO HOME

00:30.856 --> 00:32.293
and relax
and think about it?

00:32.380 --> 00:33.163
Neal: PETER.

00:35.209 --> 00:38.386
HE TOOK MY WIFE.

00:44.783 --> 00:46.481
PETER...

00:46.568 --> 00:48.483
Diana: SWAT's BEEN DEPLOYED
THROUGHOUT NEW YORK,

00:48.570 --> 00:50.006
AND HRT's ON STANDBY.

00:50.093 --> 00:52.226
WE'VE GOT AERIAL, GROUND,
MARINE, ELECTRONIC SURVEILLANCE

00:52.313 --> 00:53.314
ALL UP.

00:53.401 --> 00:54.706
CHECKPOINTS ARE EVERYWHERE.

00:54.793 --> 00:56.534
WE'LL FIND HER, PETER.

00:56.621 --> 00:58.014
DO WE KNOW
WHAT KELLER WANTS?

00:59.407 --> 01:00.277
NEAL.

01:09.895 --> 01:11.549
YOU HAVE THE TREASURE.

01:11.636 --> 01:13.247
I DIDN'T STEAL IT, OKAY?YOU SON OF A BITCH!

01:13.334 --> 01:14.770
I DON'T CARE.
YOU HAVEIT.

01:14.857 --> 01:15.988
KELLER KNOWS.

01:16.076 --> 01:17.816
YOU'RE GONNA
GIVE IT TO HIM

01:17.903 --> 01:19.383
SO THAT I CAN GET
MY WIFE BACK.

01:19.470 --> 01:20.428
YES. WHATEVER YOU NEED.MM-HMM.

01:20.515 --> 01:22.169
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

01:22.256 --> 01:23.953
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

01:24.040 --> 01:25.824
IT'S HIM.[ CELL PHONE BEEPS ]

01:25.911 --> 01:27.304
KELLER: Agent Burke.

01:27.391 --> 01:29.393
If you're smart --
and we both know you are --

01:29.480 --> 01:31.091
you'll keep the FBI
off this call.

01:31.178 --> 01:32.527
I AMFBI.

01:32.614 --> 01:35.182
No. Now you're just a man
who wants his wife back.

01:35.269 --> 01:36.966
LET ME TALK TO HER.

01:37.053 --> 01:38.576
AND WHY WOULD I
LET YOU DO THAT?

01:38.663 --> 01:39.882
I WANT TO HEAR HER VOICE.

01:43.059 --> 01:45.148
BE CAREFUL, MRS. BURKE.

01:45.235 --> 01:47.672
NO PASSING MESSAGES,
OKAY?

01:47.759 --> 01:50.675
[ SIGHS ] HI, HON.

01:50.762 --> 01:52.547
[ BREATHES SHAKILY ]

01:52.634 --> 01:53.722
HI, HON.

01:53.809 --> 01:54.940
YOU ALL RIGHT?

01:55.027 --> 01:56.681
YEAH, I-I'M OKAY.

01:56.768 --> 01:58.509
THEY HAVEN'T HURT ME.

01:58.596 --> 02:00.729
I MISS YOU.

02:00.816 --> 02:02.557
I MISS YOU, TOO.

02:02.644 --> 02:05.603
WILL YOU MAKE SURE
SATCHMO'S OKAY?

02:05.690 --> 02:07.475
You know how is
if he hasn't eaten.

02:07.562 --> 02:08.737
HEY. TALK TIME'S OVER.

02:08.824 --> 02:10.173
I'll fix this, El.

02:10.260 --> 02:12.175
EL?
[ Chuckles ]

02:12.262 --> 02:14.090
You two kids are tugging on
my heartstrings here.

02:14.177 --> 02:15.744
So nice to see
a married couple

02:15.831 --> 02:17.441
so in love
after all this time.

02:17.528 --> 02:18.964
I'D HATE TO
COME BETWEEN THAT.

02:19.051 --> 02:20.792
SO LET HER GO.I will.

02:20.879 --> 02:22.533
AS SOON AS YOU HOLD UP
YOUR END OF IT.

02:22.620 --> 02:24.492
THE MOMENT I HAVE CAFFREY'S
TREASURE, SHE'S ALL YOURS.

02:24.579 --> 02:26.146
You have 12 hours.

02:26.233 --> 02:27.234
[ CELL PHONE BEEPS ]

02:29.279 --> 02:30.672
WHAT'D SHE SAY?

02:30.759 --> 02:32.587
SHE COULD HAVE SAID
ANYTHING,

02:32.674 --> 02:34.589
AND SHE ASKED ME
ABOUT SATCHMO.

02:38.636 --> 02:40.290
HE LOOKS FINE.
I KNOW.

02:40.377 --> 02:42.336
THINK SHE WAS PASSING
A CODE?

02:42.423 --> 02:44.251
OH, THERE IT IS.

02:44.338 --> 02:46.470
OH, I LOVE MY WIFE.
RIGHT.

02:46.557 --> 02:47.819
GOOD BOY, SATCHMO.

02:47.906 --> 02:48.820
JONES!

02:48.907 --> 02:50.170
GOOD BOY.

02:50.257 --> 02:51.301
YEAH?

02:51.388 --> 02:53.303
SATCHMO BIT
ONE OF OUR KIDNAPPERS.

02:53.390 --> 02:55.436
THERE'S BLOOD
UNDER SATCHMO'S CHIN.

02:55.523 --> 02:57.351
OKAY, WE'LL GET A BLOOD KIT
AND RUN A DNA TEST.

02:57.438 --> 02:59.179
PUT WORD OUT
TO PHARMACIES AND HOSPITALS

02:59.266 --> 03:00.876
TO KEEP AN EYE OUT
FOR ANYBODY WITH A DOG BITE.

03:00.963 --> 03:01.833
THANKS.
ALL RIGHT.

03:04.488 --> 03:05.794
LET'S GO, BOY.

03:07.448 --> 03:08.449
[ SIGHS ]

03:08.536 --> 03:09.798
TAKE ME TO THE TREASURE.

03:17.632 --> 03:19.764
YOU'RE NOT GONNA TELL
THE BUREAU ABOUT KELLER?

03:19.851 --> 03:21.070
NOT YET.

03:21.157 --> 03:23.246
HE KNOWS OUR PLAYBOOK
BETTER THAN WE DO.

03:23.333 --> 03:25.944
LET JONES AND DIANA FOCUS ON
FINDING ELIZABETH.

03:26.031 --> 03:28.643
WE'LL DEAL WITH KELLER.

03:28.730 --> 03:30.035
WHEW!

03:30.122 --> 03:32.777
I DRIVE PAST THIS BUILDING
EVERY MORNING.

03:32.864 --> 03:34.605
THE TREASURE'S IN HERE?

03:34.692 --> 03:36.999
I DIDN'T ASK FOR IT.

03:37.086 --> 03:38.653
YOU COULD HAVE
WALKED AWAY.

03:38.740 --> 03:40.698
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I COULD HAVE.

03:40.785 --> 03:43.571
I DIDN'T.

03:43.658 --> 03:45.834
AND I SHOULD BE PAYING FOR IT,
NOT ELIZABETH.

03:45.921 --> 03:48.228
YOU'RE GOING TO PAY
FOR IT. RIGHT NOW.

03:48.315 --> 03:50.186
[ KEYPAD BEEPING ]

03:50.273 --> 03:52.188
[ BUZZER ]

03:59.326 --> 04:00.457
WHERE IS IT?

04:00.544 --> 04:01.719
IT WAS HERE.

04:04.026 --> 04:05.070
PETER,
IT WAS ALL HERE.

04:05.157 --> 04:06.942
OH, GOD.

04:08.726 --> 04:09.988
HE ALREADY MOVED IT.

04:10.075 --> 04:11.773
WHO'S "HE"?
HE? MOZZIE?

04:11.860 --> 04:14.166
OF COURSE IT WAS MOZZIE.
YOU CALL HIM.

04:14.254 --> 04:16.343
I TRIED.

04:16.430 --> 04:19.041
LOOK, HE'S NOT TALKING TO ME.
WE HAD A FALLING OUT.

04:19.128 --> 04:21.304
WHAT, YOU COULDN'T AGREE ON
WHAT ISLAND TO BUY?

04:21.391 --> 04:23.828
I DIDN'T THINK HE'D MOVE IT
THIS FAST.

04:26.178 --> 04:27.267
WHERE'D HE TAKE IT?

04:27.354 --> 04:28.572
I DON'T KNOW.

04:28.659 --> 04:30.574
I DON'T.

04:30.661 --> 04:32.620
IT'S ELIZABETH.
NO LIES. I DON'T KNOW.

04:32.707 --> 04:34.056
UGH!

04:34.143 --> 04:35.405
DAMN IT, NEAL!

04:38.582 --> 04:40.236
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

04:40.323 --> 04:42.151
MOZZIE COULD BE ANYWHERE
IN THE WORLD.

04:42.238 --> 04:44.284
WE HAVE LESS THAN 12 HOURS
TO FIND HIM.
PETER.

04:46.416 --> 04:47.504
WE'RE GONNA GET HER BACK.

04:47.591 --> 04:50.246
AND WE START
BY FINDING MOZZIE.

05:10.266 --> 05:11.659
[ CELL PHONE CHIRPS ]

05:14.009 --> 05:15.402
[ SIGHS ]

05:17.491 --> 05:19.623
Peter: ANY LUCK
IN FINDING MOZZIE?

05:19.710 --> 05:21.843
NO. HE'S GONE
COMPLETELY TO GROUND.

05:21.930 --> 05:24.193
HE'S CANCELED HIS EMAILS,
HIS CELL PHONES.

05:24.280 --> 05:25.455
YOU FIND ANYTHING?

05:25.542 --> 05:27.152
NOPE. HIS SAFE HOUSES
ARE ABANDONED.

05:27.239 --> 05:28.240
MONDAY THROUGH SUNDAY?

05:28.328 --> 05:29.329
EMPTY.

05:29.416 --> 05:30.982
HE PROBABLY
LEFT THE CITY.

05:31.069 --> 05:32.114
[ SIGHS ]

05:39.948 --> 05:42.124
WHAT WERE YOU TWO
ARGUING ABOUT?

05:42.211 --> 05:45.823
MOZZIE WANTED TO LEAVE
NEW YORK.

05:45.910 --> 05:46.824
I DIDN'T.

05:46.911 --> 05:48.783
WHY NOT?

05:49.871 --> 05:50.785
YOU.

05:52.352 --> 05:54.136
ELIZABETH.

05:54.223 --> 05:56.791
SARA.

05:56.878 --> 05:58.532
THE VIEW
OUT THAT WINDOW.

05:58.619 --> 06:00.664
STEPPING OFF THE ELEVATOR
MONDAY MORNING.

06:00.751 --> 06:02.144
ALL OF IT.

06:04.059 --> 06:05.495
I HAVE A LIFE HERE.

06:08.106 --> 06:10.021
WHAT ABOUT MOZZIE?

06:10.108 --> 06:13.198
WELL, HE DIDN'T LIKE
TO ADMIT IT, BUT, YEAH...

06:13.285 --> 06:14.678
THIS IS HIS HOME.

06:14.765 --> 06:18.769
I RAN EVERY ALIAS
YOU GAVE ME.

06:18.856 --> 06:21.250
HE HASN'T BOARDED A PLANE
OR A BOAT.

06:21.337 --> 06:22.817
THAT MEANS
HE'S THINKING IT OVER.

06:22.904 --> 06:25.210
WHERE?
HE WANTS SECLUSION.

06:25.297 --> 06:27.865
THERE'S GOT TO BE A WAY
TO REACH HIM.
THERE IS.

06:27.952 --> 06:29.345
ONE WAY.

06:29.432 --> 06:30.999
[ AIR HORN BLOWS ]

06:36.221 --> 06:37.745
I'M LOOKING FOR
ESTELLE.

06:37.832 --> 06:40.269
STRANGE PLACE TO FIND A WOMAN,
DON'T YOU THINK?

06:40.356 --> 06:43.577
SHE'S NOT A WOMAN,
BUT YOU ALREADY KNOW THAT.

06:43.664 --> 06:45.927
ALL RIGHT. WHO ARE YOU?

06:46.014 --> 06:47.276
FRIEND OF MOZZIE'S.

06:47.363 --> 06:49.278
I NEED TO GET
A MESSAGE TO HIM.

06:49.365 --> 06:52.324
BLUE EYES.
TAILORED SUIT.

06:52.412 --> 06:54.239
HE TOLD ME
YOU MIGHT COME.

06:54.326 --> 06:55.893
HE SAID TO SEND YOU AWAY.

06:57.982 --> 06:59.201
CHER AMI.

07:00.811 --> 07:02.030
DURING WORLD WAR I,

07:02.117 --> 07:03.640
THE LOST BATTALION
WAS SURROUNDED

07:03.727 --> 07:05.642
BY GERMAN SOLDIERS
IN THE BATTLE OF ARGONNE.

07:05.729 --> 07:08.166
EVERY CARRIER PIGEON THEY
SENT OUT FOR HELP WAS KILLED.

07:08.253 --> 07:09.733
CHER AMI
WAS THEIR LAST ONE.

07:09.820 --> 07:12.257
THE LOST BATTALION WATCHED HIM
GET SHOT DOWN.

07:12.344 --> 07:13.345
ALL HOPE WAS LOST.

07:13.433 --> 07:14.738
BUT SOMEHOW,

07:14.825 --> 07:17.045
HE TOOK FLIGHT AGAIN
AND REACHED HIS DESTINATION.

07:17.132 --> 07:18.568
SAVED 200 LIVES

07:18.655 --> 07:21.571
AND WAS AWARDED
THE CROIX DE GUERRE.

07:21.658 --> 07:23.704
CHER AMIMEANS
"DEAR FRIEND."

07:23.791 --> 07:26.097
MOZZIE'S DEAR FRIEND
NEEDS HIM NOW.

07:26.184 --> 07:28.056
HE DOESN'T KNOW IT,

07:28.143 --> 07:30.014
BUT ANOTHER LIFE
NEEDS TO BE SAVED.

07:39.720 --> 07:40.895
HEY, ESTELLE.

07:40.982 --> 07:44.768
IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME.

07:44.855 --> 07:47.597
I NEVER KNEW WHERE YOU FLEW TO,
BUT I THINK I DO NOW.

07:50.208 --> 07:51.471
MOZZIE ALWAYS SAID

07:51.558 --> 07:53.647
YOU WERE THE BEST HOMER
IN THE CITY.

07:53.734 --> 07:54.561
WE NEED YOU.

08:06.268 --> 08:08.226
MORNING.

08:08.313 --> 08:09.097
THOUGHT YOU COULD USE
A FRESH CUP.

08:09.184 --> 08:10.620
THANKS, JONES.

08:10.707 --> 08:13.449
DNA RESULTS CAME BACK
ON THE BLOOD FROM SATCHMO.

08:13.536 --> 08:14.929
IT WASN'T KELLER'S.

08:15.016 --> 08:15.973
[ SIGHS ]

08:16.060 --> 08:17.584
LEONARD GRANT.

08:17.671 --> 08:20.282
Jones: GRANT HAS A HISTORY
OF UNPREDICTABLE VIOLENCE.

08:20.369 --> 08:22.980
HE HAS A LONG RAP SHEET,
INCLUDING KIDNAPPING.

08:23.067 --> 08:24.852
LOOKS LIKE THE KIND OF GUY
KELLER WOULD LOVE.

08:24.939 --> 08:26.114
EXACTLY.

08:26.201 --> 08:27.376
WE'RE LOOKING INTO
HIS FORMER CONTACTS NOW,

08:27.463 --> 08:28.769
TRACING
HIS FINANCIAL HISTORY.

08:28.856 --> 08:29.726
GOOD.

08:32.816 --> 08:36.211
BOSS, IS THERE ANYTHING
I CAN DO FOR YOU?

08:36.298 --> 08:39.083
[ Sighing ] OH...
EXACTLY WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

08:39.170 --> 08:41.477
THERE ISN'T ANYONE
I TRUST MORE

08:41.564 --> 08:43.871
TO SPEARHEAD THIS
THAN YOU AND JONES.

08:43.958 --> 08:44.785
WHAT ABOUT CAFFREY?

08:46.438 --> 08:48.092
HE HAS THE TREASURE,
DOESN'T HE?

08:48.179 --> 08:50.660
THAT'S WHAT KELLER'S AFTER,
AND YOU'RE WORKING THAT ANGLE.

08:50.747 --> 08:53.489
THE LESS YOU KNOW, THE BETTER
RIGHT NOW.

08:53.576 --> 08:55.491
THANKS, DIANA.

08:55.578 --> 08:56.753
OKAY.

09:01.366 --> 09:03.194
[ HORNS HONKING,
SIRENS WAILING ]

09:12.595 --> 09:14.379
[ WINGS FLAPPING ]

09:14.466 --> 09:16.294
[ ESTELLE COOS ]

09:16.381 --> 09:18.470
OH, ESTELLE.
YOU'RE EARLY.

09:38.926 --> 09:40.623
PLEASE...
DON'T HURT ME.

09:40.710 --> 09:42.756
T-THEY'LL GIVE YOU
WHAT YOU WANT.

09:42.843 --> 09:44.061
THEY BETTER,

09:44.148 --> 09:45.846
'CAUSE I GOT
LOTS OF DEBTS TO PAY...

09:45.933 --> 09:47.717
ESPECIALLY TO
THE RUSSIANS,

09:47.804 --> 09:49.763
SO HOPEFULLY THIS WILL
CLEAR THEM ALL

09:49.850 --> 09:51.242
IN ONE FELL SWOOP.

09:51.329 --> 09:54.594
BESIDES, THE ART DOESN'T
BELONG TO NEAL ANYWAY.

09:54.681 --> 09:56.813
HE'S JUST THE MOST RECENT PERSON
TO STEAL IT.

09:56.900 --> 09:58.641
I'M GLAD
YOU'RE TAKING IT.

09:58.728 --> 10:00.295
YOU ARE, HUH?

10:00.382 --> 10:01.992
WHY DO YOU SAY THAT?

10:02.079 --> 10:04.212
NEAL BETRAYED MY HUSBAND,
LIED TO HIM.

10:04.299 --> 10:05.953
HE DOESN'T DESERVE
ANY OF IT.

10:06.040 --> 10:07.389
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:07.476 --> 10:10.174
WOW, YOU'RE GOOD,
MRS. B.

10:10.261 --> 10:12.263
I'LL GIVE YOU THAT.

10:12.350 --> 10:14.483
NO EYE CONTACT,
IDENTIFYING WITH YOUR CAPTOR.

10:14.570 --> 10:16.572
I MEAN, YOU HAVEN'T EVEN
USED MY NAME.

10:16.659 --> 10:19.314
EVERYTHING FROM THE FBI
KIDNAPPING PLAYBOOK, HUH?

10:19.401 --> 10:21.272
THE ONLY PROBLEM IS...

10:21.359 --> 10:25.059
YOUR HUSBAND ALREADY KNOWS
WHO I AM.

10:26.234 --> 10:28.453
THAT'S TRUE.

10:28.540 --> 10:31.413
AND HE AND NEAL
ARE GOING TO KICK YOUR ASS.

10:33.720 --> 10:36.070
WELL, LISTEN, I'M SURE
YOU'RE TRYING TO FIGURE OUT

10:36.157 --> 10:37.593
HOW TO ESCAPE FROM HERE,

10:37.680 --> 10:39.682
SO LET ME MAKE THIS
NICE AND EASY.

10:39.769 --> 10:41.945
THIS DOOR IS YOUR ONLY WAY
IN AND OUT.

10:42.032 --> 10:44.034
NOT EVEN NEAL
COULD PICK THIS LOCK.

10:44.121 --> 10:46.689
IF I WERE YOU,

10:46.776 --> 10:51.085
MY SECOND CHOICE WOULD BE
THIS HERE FIRE ESCAPE.

10:54.784 --> 10:57.700
SO UNLESS YOU HAVE A DRILL KIT
HIDDEN IN YOUR BLOUSE,

10:57.787 --> 11:00.050
THIS IS WHERE
YOU'RE STAYING.

11:00.137 --> 11:01.356
BUT JUST TO MAKE SURE --

11:01.443 --> 11:02.270
HEY, GRANT!

11:05.229 --> 11:06.753
I BELIEVE YOU TWO
MET EARLIER, RIGHT?

11:06.840 --> 11:09.190
I'D SHAKE YOUR HAND,
BUT...

11:09.277 --> 11:10.800
SO WHILE I'M OUT
MEETING YOUR HUSBAND,

11:10.887 --> 11:13.281
GRANT HERE WILL BE KEEPING
AN EYE ON YOU.

11:15.065 --> 11:16.719
HOW LONG
YOU GONNA BE GONE?
WHAT?

11:16.806 --> 11:18.416
MY HAND IS REALLY
STARTING TO HURT.

11:18.503 --> 11:20.114
IT'S A SCRATCH.

11:26.860 --> 11:28.775
GOOD-BYE,
ELIZABETH BURKE.

11:31.255 --> 11:34.345
SHOOT HER IN THE FOOT
IF SHE TRIES ANYTHING.

11:34.432 --> 11:35.912
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

11:44.312 --> 11:46.967
I WANT TO BE PREPARED
IF WE CAN'T FIND MOZZIE.

11:47.054 --> 11:49.099
WHAT IF WE TELL KELLER
THE TRUTH?

11:49.186 --> 11:50.971
HE'LL THINK
WE'RE STALLING.

11:51.058 --> 11:53.277
AND HE'LL TAKE IT OUT
ON ELIZABETH.

11:53.364 --> 11:56.454
Maybe we should let the FBI know
what Keller wants.

11:56.541 --> 11:58.587
They won't negotiate
with kidnappers,

11:58.674 --> 12:00.720
and I want them focusing
on finding El.

12:00.807 --> 12:03.461
[ SIGHS ]

12:03.548 --> 12:06.464
WELL, WE DON'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT FINDING MOZZIE.

12:06.551 --> 12:07.814
LET'S GET HIM UP HERE NOW.

12:13.733 --> 12:15.604
FOR ONCE, WORDS FAIL ME.

12:15.691 --> 12:18.955
THEY CAN'T POSSIBLY CONVEY
HOW SORRY I AM.

12:19.042 --> 12:20.914
THIS WAS KELLER'S BIG MOVE.
I SHOULD HAVE SEEN THIS COMING.

12:21.001 --> 12:21.828
Peter:
DO YOU HAVE THE TREASURE?

12:21.915 --> 12:23.743
YEP.
GOOD.

12:23.830 --> 12:25.962
WAIT! Y-YOU CAN'T
GIVE IT TO HIM.

12:26.049 --> 12:27.398
NO, NO. ONCE HE HAS IT,
THERE'S NO REASON --

12:27.485 --> 12:28.704
ONCE HE HAS IT,

12:28.791 --> 12:30.184
THERE'S NO REASON
TO KEEP HER ALIVE!

12:30.271 --> 12:31.925
HE DIDN'T EVEN HESITATE
TO KILL HALE.

12:32.012 --> 12:33.448
HE'S RIGHT, OKAY?

12:33.535 --> 12:36.103
BUT NOW WE HAVE THE TREASURE
AS A BARGAINING CHIP.

12:36.190 --> 12:37.408
EL'S ONLY CHANCE,

12:37.495 --> 12:39.454
MY ONLY GUARANTEE
THAT SHE'LL BE SAFE

12:39.541 --> 12:40.934
IS IF THE FBI FINDS HER.

12:41.021 --> 12:42.283
WE'RE RUNNING OUT
OF TIME, PETER.

12:42.370 --> 12:43.675
WE NEED TO BUY MORE TIME.

12:43.763 --> 12:46.156
YEAH, BUT KELLER'S SMART ENOUGH
TO READ A STALL.

12:46.243 --> 12:48.245
THEN THE THREE OF US HAVE TO BE
SMARTER THAN HIM.

12:48.332 --> 12:49.377
WE'VE BEEN PLAYING
BY KELLER'S RULES.

12:51.205 --> 12:52.554
LET'S CHANGE THE GAME.

13:05.306 --> 13:06.394
THOUGHT YOU'D BE

13:06.481 --> 13:08.091
SIPPING MAI TAIS
ON A BEACH BY NOW.

13:08.178 --> 13:09.440
AFTER ALL THAT HAPPENED,

13:09.527 --> 13:11.703
I THOUGHT SOME INTROSPECTION
WAS IN ORDER.

13:11.791 --> 13:14.271
I DECIDED TO FOLLOW
IN THE FOOTSTEPS OF THOREAU.

13:14.358 --> 13:16.578
FOUND YOURSELF A NICE POND
AND LIVED OFF THE LAND?

13:16.665 --> 13:19.407
ADMIT IT.
IT'S A HARD CITY TO LEAVE.

13:19.494 --> 13:21.409
SHE'S
A STUBBORN MISTRESS.

13:23.715 --> 13:25.282
GO THROUGH
GRANT'S ACCOUNTS.

13:25.369 --> 13:27.371
LOOK FOR ANYTHING
THAT MAY BE A SAFE HOUSE.

13:27.458 --> 13:30.287
THIS IS MY FAULT.NO, IT'S MINE.

13:30.374 --> 13:32.420
I WAS THE ONE WHO TOOK
THE TREASURE IN THE FIRST PLACE.

13:32.507 --> 13:33.943
KELLER KIDNAPPED ELIZABETH.
YOU DIDN'T.

13:34.030 --> 13:35.640
REMEMBER THAT.

13:35.727 --> 13:36.859
WHAT'D THE FBI SAY?

13:36.946 --> 13:39.166
THEY HAVE A LEAD,
BUT THEY NEED MORE TIME.

13:39.253 --> 13:40.907
WE CAN'T
STALL THE EXCHANGE.

13:40.994 --> 13:43.083
PETER, IF WE DO,
THERE'S NO TELLING

13:43.170 --> 13:46.303
WHAT KELLER WOULD DO
TO ELIZABETH.

13:46.390 --> 13:48.566
WHERE ARE YOU KEEPING
THE TREASURE?

13:48.653 --> 13:51.874
IT'S IN A SECURE FACILITY
I SET UP WITH SOME ASSOCIATES.

13:51.961 --> 13:53.571
WHAT IF WE
STALLED KELLER

13:53.658 --> 13:55.530
WITHOUT APPEARING
TO STALL HIM?

13:55.617 --> 13:57.271
WELL, IT'D HAVE TO BE SOMETHING
OUT OF OUR CONTROL.

13:57.358 --> 13:58.750
KELLER'S NOT
AN EASY ONE TO CON.

13:58.838 --> 14:01.231
YEAH, HE'D HAVE TO THINK
WE WERE OPERATING IN GOOD FAITH.

14:01.318 --> 14:02.537
[ SIGHS ]

14:02.624 --> 14:04.147
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO SHOW HIM
THE TREASURE.

14:04.234 --> 14:05.670
I HAVE AN IDEA.

14:05.757 --> 14:09.152
WE'LL NEED A WELL-TIMED CALL
TO THE POLICE

14:09.239 --> 14:11.676
AND A CRIMINAL WE HAVE
NO CONCRETE TIES TO --

14:11.763 --> 14:13.678
SOMEONE YOU WOULDN'T MIND
RATTING OUT.

14:14.941 --> 14:16.681
I KNOW JUST THE RAT.

14:24.080 --> 14:25.386
Rufus:
MOZZIE, I MUST SAY,

14:25.473 --> 14:26.953
AFTER WHAT HAPPENED
IN ATLANTA,

14:27.040 --> 14:28.563
I'M SURPRISED
TO HEAR FROM YOU.

14:28.650 --> 14:31.087
YEAH, WELL, DESPERATION
MAKES FOR STRANGE BEDFELLOWS.

14:31.174 --> 14:33.481
UM, CAN I TALK TO YOU
WITHOUT YOUR SHADOW?

14:33.568 --> 14:34.351
SIMON.

14:36.266 --> 14:38.703
LOOK, I HAVE A TWO-MAN JOB
THAT NEEDS TO BE DONE TODAY.

14:38.790 --> 14:40.705
I NEED SOMEONE WHO CAN CRACK
THE BEST SECURITY.

14:40.792 --> 14:42.142
WHAT IS THE JOB?

14:42.229 --> 14:44.187
IT'S A BENEFACTOR-SPECIFIED
TARGET.

14:44.274 --> 14:46.407
I JUST PICKED UP THE PACKAGE
ON THE WAY HERE.

14:46.494 --> 14:47.625
WAIT A MINUTE.

14:47.712 --> 14:48.670
SO YOU HAVEN'T ACTUALLY
OPENED IT?

14:48.757 --> 14:50.063
NO,
I WAS RUNNING LATE --

14:50.150 --> 14:51.760
SO YOU DON'T ACTUALLY KNOW
WHAT THE JOB IS?

14:51.847 --> 14:53.153
I'M SURE
EVERYTHING'S IN HERE.

14:53.240 --> 14:54.545
I'VE WORKED
FOR THIS GUY BEFORE.

14:54.632 --> 14:56.504
HE'S LEGIT.

14:56.591 --> 14:57.722
I BELIEVE YOU.

14:59.681 --> 15:01.204
OH, COME ON, RUFUS.

15:01.291 --> 15:03.598
WE BOTH HAVE A CHANCE
TO MAKE SOME SERIOUS CASH HERE.

15:03.685 --> 15:05.643
WELL, SINCE YOU ACTUALLY
DON'T KNOW WHAT THE JOB IS,

15:05.730 --> 15:07.732
I GUESS THAT
I'M GONNA BE THE ONE

15:07.819 --> 15:10.344
MAKING THE SERIOUS SCRATCH,
AND SIMON, TOO.

15:10.431 --> 15:13.347
Simon: THANKS
FOR YOUR HELP, MATE.

15:13.434 --> 15:14.696
DAMN YOU, RUFUS!

15:27.665 --> 15:28.971
HOW'S YOUR HEART RATE?

15:29.058 --> 15:31.321
WHAT?

15:31.408 --> 15:35.064
IF IT'S INFECTED,
YOUR HEART RATE WILL INCREASE.

15:35.151 --> 15:36.283
IT'S A SCRATCH.

15:36.370 --> 15:37.501
MM. YOU'RE RIGHT.

15:37.588 --> 15:38.938
I'M SURE YOU'RE FINE.

15:39.025 --> 15:41.288
UNLESS
YOU START SWEATING.

15:43.116 --> 15:44.334
AND IF THAT HAPPENS?

15:44.421 --> 15:45.509
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

15:45.596 --> 15:46.858
WELL [SIGHS]

15:46.946 --> 15:48.817
IT'S PROBABLY
BLOOD POISONING.

15:48.904 --> 15:50.253
VERY COMMON
IN DOG BITES.

15:50.340 --> 15:51.515
BUT YOU DON'T
HAVE TO BELIEVE ME.

15:51.602 --> 15:52.734
YOU CAN LOOK IT UP
ON YOUR PHONE.

15:59.262 --> 16:02.004
Neal: YOU PICTURING YOURSELF
SHOOTING KELLER RIGHT NOW?

16:02.091 --> 16:04.180
Peter: NO.
I DON'T WANT TO SHOOT HIM.

16:04.267 --> 16:06.530
I WANT TO SMASH IN HIS FACE
REPEATEDLY.

16:06.617 --> 16:09.577
Mozzie: I'M CURRENTLY STICKING
BAMBOO UNDER HIS FINGERNAILS.

16:09.664 --> 16:11.405
YOU ARE ONE
FOR THE CLASSICS.

16:11.492 --> 16:12.884
Keller: YOU GUYS
TALKING ABOUT ME?

16:12.972 --> 16:14.190
'CAUSE MY EARS
ARE BURNING.

16:14.277 --> 16:15.713
[ BREATHING DEEPLY ]

16:15.800 --> 16:17.454
MY WIFE BETTER BE SAFE.

16:17.541 --> 16:18.890
I LIKE TO SEE
THE PASSION, BURKE.

16:18.978 --> 16:20.153
IT SHOWS ME
YOU'RE MOTIVATED.

16:20.240 --> 16:21.371
LOOK, SHE'S FINE.

16:21.458 --> 16:23.199
AS LONG AS I CALL IN
EVERY HALF HOUR,

16:23.286 --> 16:24.331
SHE'LL STAY THAT WAY.

16:24.418 --> 16:25.593
IS YOUR DOG
OFF HIS LEASH?

16:26.724 --> 16:28.639
NO ANKLET.

16:28.726 --> 16:30.772
GOOD BOY.

16:30.859 --> 16:31.903
SO THE TREASURE'S HERE?

16:31.991 --> 16:33.253
IT DON'T LOOK LIKE MUCH,
MOZZIE.

16:33.340 --> 16:35.255
THAT'S PRECISELY
THE POINT.

16:43.959 --> 16:45.308
WHAT IS THIS PLACE?

16:45.395 --> 16:48.268
IT'S A STORAGE SPACE
FOR HONORABLE THIEVES --

16:48.355 --> 16:51.271
THE KIND WHO WOULDN'T STEAL
FROM OTHER THIEVES.

16:51.358 --> 16:53.664
Keller: NO SUCH THING,
SWEETHEART.

16:53.751 --> 16:56.450
MUST HAVE BEEN HARD FOR YOU,
CAFFREY, HUH?

16:56.537 --> 16:57.799
LYING
TO YOUR FRIEND'S FACE

16:57.886 --> 16:59.583
ABOUT HAVING THE TREASURE
ALL THIS TIME?

16:59.670 --> 17:01.455
Peter: WE CAN DO THIS
WITHOUT THE COMMENTARY.

17:01.542 --> 17:02.804
YOU'VE ALWAYS BEEN GOOD

17:02.891 --> 17:04.414
AT LYING TO THOSE
CLOSEST TO YOU.

17:04.501 --> 17:05.285
RIGHT, MOZ?

17:06.895 --> 17:08.418
WELCOME
TO CONTAINER 10...

17:08.505 --> 17:09.289
SWEETHEART.

17:12.683 --> 17:15.251
THIS IS IT.

17:15.338 --> 17:17.601
THE SCORE OF A LIFETIME.

17:30.658 --> 17:33.269
WHAT DO WE HAVE HERE?

17:33.356 --> 17:35.663
NAPOLEON BROUGHT THAT BACK
FROM HIS EGYPT EXPEDITION.

17:35.750 --> 17:37.056
IT WAS IN
HIS PRIVATE COLLECTION.

17:37.143 --> 17:38.144
YEAH?

17:38.231 --> 17:40.494
NOW IT'S IN MINE.

17:40.581 --> 17:42.757
I MEAN, ALL THIS TIME,
CAFFREY,

17:42.844 --> 17:44.802
YOU HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE
TO SEE IT IN PERSON,

17:44.889 --> 17:47.022
AND NOW YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO WATCH ME TAKE IT AWAY.

17:47.109 --> 17:47.979
[ SIREN WAILING ]

17:48.067 --> 17:49.590
COPS?
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

17:49.677 --> 17:51.331
YOU THINK
I WAS BLUFFING, BURKE?

17:51.418 --> 17:53.202
NO.

17:53.289 --> 17:55.857
YOUR WIFE IS DEAD
IN FIVE MINUTES IF I
DON'T MAKE THAT CALL.

17:55.944 --> 17:57.119
AND I'M NOT GONNA BE ABLE
TO DO THAT

17:57.206 --> 17:58.120
WITH CUFFS
AROUND MY WRISTS.

17:58.207 --> 17:59.513
THIS WASN'T US, KELLER.

17:59.600 --> 18:00.644
WELL, WE CAN'T GET CAUGHT
HERE. LET'S GO.

18:06.041 --> 18:07.869
Officer: POLICE!ALL RIGHT, BUDDY, GO AHEAD.

18:09.827 --> 18:11.525
THERE SHOULD BE TWO
IN THE BACK!

18:11.612 --> 18:13.483
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

18:13.570 --> 18:14.702
YOU TWO, FREEZE!

18:14.789 --> 18:17.052
Rufus: HEY, COME ON.
COME ON. HANDS OFF!

18:17.139 --> 18:19.489
WE FOUND THESE GUYS BREAKING
INTO THIS SHIPPING CONTAINER.

18:19.576 --> 18:21.491
OFFICER,
WE WEREN'T BREAKING IN.

18:21.578 --> 18:23.145
NOT AT ALL.
WE OWN THIS.

18:23.232 --> 18:24.494
DO YOU ALSO OWN
THE PRINTING PRESS

18:24.581 --> 18:25.887
AND THE COUNTERFEIT $20s
INSIDE?

18:25.974 --> 18:27.715
HEOWNS IT.I'VE NEVER SEEN IT.

18:27.802 --> 18:28.890
YOU DRAGGED ME
INTO THIS.ALL RIGHT.

18:28.977 --> 18:29.760
SHUT UP!

18:31.588 --> 18:33.199
I THINK WE SHOULD CHECK OUT
THE REST OF THE CONTAINERS.

18:36.767 --> 18:37.942
I'LL GET YOU.

18:38.029 --> 18:39.553
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

18:43.034 --> 18:44.210
YOU GUYS DID THIS.

18:44.297 --> 18:46.212
YOU THINK
I WOULD PLAY GAMES

18:46.299 --> 18:48.301
WITH MY WIFE'S LIFE
ON THE LINE?

18:48.388 --> 18:49.780
THIS WASN'T US.

18:49.867 --> 18:53.044
SO, WHAT, THIS IS JUST
SOME RANDOM MISFORTUNE?

18:53.132 --> 18:54.742
WE MADE A DEAL, KELLER.

18:54.829 --> 18:57.397
YOU HAVE THE TREASURE,
RELEASE MY WIFE.

18:57.484 --> 18:59.442
I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING,
BURKE.

18:59.529 --> 19:00.574
THE COPS DO.

19:00.661 --> 19:02.228
THEY'RE SETTING UP
A PERIMETER,

19:02.315 --> 19:04.795
WHICH MEANS THEY'LL OPEN
EVERY CONTAINER.

19:04.882 --> 19:08.103
WELL, THE POLICE WILL NEED
WARRANTS TO GET INTO THEM.

19:08.190 --> 19:10.323
THAT SHOULD BUY US
SOME TIME.

19:10.410 --> 19:12.716
FOR WHAT?

19:12.803 --> 19:16.416
THE THREE OF YOU DO WHAT
YOU DO BEST -- STEAL IT.

19:21.812 --> 19:23.162
NOT THE THREE OF US.

19:23.249 --> 19:25.816
THE FOUROF US.

19:25.903 --> 19:28.906
I'M AN FBI AGENT.

19:28.993 --> 19:31.170
TODAY,
YOU'RE ONE OF US.

19:31.257 --> 19:33.737
BOYS, WE'RE GONNA
STEAL BACK

19:33.824 --> 19:35.261
OUR STOLEN TREASURE.

19:44.183 --> 19:46.010
NO BEER?

19:46.097 --> 19:47.664
CAFFREY,
YOU'RE A TERRIBLE HOST.

19:47.751 --> 19:49.144
THAT'S 'CAUSE I DON'T WANT
YOU HERE TO BEGIN WITH.

19:49.231 --> 19:50.624
OH, I KNOW.

19:50.711 --> 19:53.061
BEFORE I DISAPPEAR
WITH ALL YOUR ILL-GOTTEN GOODS,

19:53.148 --> 19:55.368
I WANTED TO SEE
WHERE YOU'VE BEEN HOLED UP.

19:55.455 --> 19:57.065
MAN, OH, MAN,
YOU'VE BEEN SLUMMING IT.

19:57.152 --> 19:58.109
CAN WE FOCUS?

19:58.197 --> 19:59.241
THE TREASURE'S
IN CONTAINER 10.

19:59.328 --> 20:00.721
10, HUH?

20:00.808 --> 20:02.853
"X" MARKS THE SPOT.
YOU GET IT? [ CHUCKLES ]

20:02.940 --> 20:04.333
HMM.

20:04.420 --> 20:05.943
POLICE MADE
THEIR ARREST HERE.

20:06.030 --> 20:07.467
THIS CONTAINER
WAS ALREADY OPEN,

20:07.554 --> 20:09.164
SO THEY WERE ABLE
TO SEARCH IT.

20:09.251 --> 20:12.385
THEY FILED FOR WARRANTS
FOR EVERY OTHER CONTAINER.

20:12.472 --> 20:14.213
THOSE SHOULD TAKE A DAY.

20:14.300 --> 20:16.650
WHICH MEANS WE GOT TO MOVE
THE TREASURE FAST, HUH?

20:16.737 --> 20:17.825
FOR HIS WIFE'S SAKE.

20:19.566 --> 20:21.959
ALL RIGHT,
HERE'S THE POLICE PERIMETER.

20:22.046 --> 20:24.701
THERE'S ONE GUARD POST OUT FRONT
TO LET PEOPLE IN AND OUT.

20:24.788 --> 20:26.703
THERE'S A SHIFT CHANGE
AT LUNCH.

20:26.790 --> 20:29.489
EVERY HALF HOUR, THE POLICE
WILL ONLY BE STATIONED

20:29.576 --> 20:30.664
OUTSIDE THE BUILDING.

20:30.751 --> 20:31.926
THAT'S OUR WINDOW.

20:32.013 --> 20:33.406
STANDARD POLICE PROCEDURE

20:33.493 --> 20:34.929
IS THEY CHECK EVERY HOUR,
ON THE HOUR.

20:35.016 --> 20:36.104
SO, WE SUBDUE THE GUARDS

20:36.191 --> 20:37.758
AND THEN WE DRIVE
THE TRUCK IN -- BOOM.

20:37.845 --> 20:39.890
AND HOW DO YOU PLAN
TO SUBDUE THE COPS?

20:39.977 --> 20:41.544
A BULLET IN EACH HEAD.

20:41.631 --> 20:43.024
NO. NO KILLING.

20:43.111 --> 20:45.461
IN FACT,
NO GUNS AT ALL.

20:45.548 --> 20:47.550
OH, PETER, PETER, PETER.
CAN I CALL YOU PETER?

20:47.637 --> 20:49.378
NOW THAT WE'RE
WORKING TOGETHER AND ALL, HUH?

20:49.465 --> 20:52.599
THE COPS WOULD HAVE SEEN
OUR FACES, PETER.

20:52.686 --> 20:54.296
DEAD MEN DON'T TALK.

20:54.383 --> 20:56.255
I WILL NOT LET ANYONE
DIE ON THIS.

20:56.342 --> 20:57.691
THAT'S NOT UP FOR DEBATE.

20:57.778 --> 21:01.042
ALL RIGHT, RELAX.
NO GUNS.

21:01.129 --> 21:02.826
IT'S PROBABLY
FOR THE BEST, HUH?

21:02.913 --> 21:05.220
THE LITTLE GUY'S
TRIED TO KILL ME ONCE ALREADY.

21:05.307 --> 21:06.395
YEAH, IS THERE ANYONE
IN THIS ROOM

21:06.482 --> 21:07.353
YOU HAVEN'T TRIED
TO KILL?

21:07.440 --> 21:08.745
YOU.

21:08.832 --> 21:10.312
YET.

21:10.399 --> 21:11.879
BUT IT'S STARTING TO
CROSS MY MIND, MOZZIE.

21:13.620 --> 21:16.231
SO, HOW DO YOU SUGGEST
WE GET IN?

21:16.318 --> 21:18.799
FBI RECEIVED THIS
AN HOUR AGO.

21:18.886 --> 21:20.540
THE POLICE ARE ASKING
TO BORROW CARGO TRUCKS

21:20.627 --> 21:22.977
FROM OTHER BRANCHES
OF THE GOVERNMENT.

21:23.064 --> 21:24.283
THIS IS OUR IN.

21:24.370 --> 21:25.545
ALL RIGHT, I MEAN,

21:25.632 --> 21:27.590
WE CAN GET THROUGH
THE PERIMETER WITH THAT,

21:27.677 --> 21:29.940
BUT THEY'RE NOT GONNA LET US
RUN AROUND UNSUPERVISED.

21:30.027 --> 21:31.290
BUT THEY'LL LEAVE

21:31.377 --> 21:32.726
WHAT APPEARS TO BE
AN EMPTY TRUCK UNMOLESTED.

21:32.813 --> 21:35.119
BARCELONA, 2001, HUH?

21:35.206 --> 21:36.904
THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE THINKING,
ISN'T IT?

21:36.991 --> 21:38.384
IT WAS MADRID.
BUT, YEAH.

21:38.471 --> 21:40.690
YOU SHOULD HAVE SEEN IT.
CAFFREY WAS AMAZING, RIGHT?

21:40.777 --> 21:42.475
WE WERE SCAMMING THIS COIN --LET'S STAY ON TASK.

21:42.562 --> 21:45.042
YOU AND MOZ WILL CON THE TRUCK
PAST THE COPS.

21:45.129 --> 21:46.914
ONCE THE TRUCK IS ALONE,

21:47.001 --> 21:49.090
PETER AND I WILL EMERGE
FROM OUR HIDING PLACE
AND GRAB THE TREASURE.

21:49.177 --> 21:50.657
YOU AND PETER?

21:50.744 --> 21:52.267
NICE TRY, KID.

21:53.834 --> 21:56.184
IT'LL BE YOU AND I
STOWING AWAY TOGETHER.

21:56.271 --> 21:57.751
IT WILL BE LIKE OLD TIMES.

21:57.838 --> 21:59.187
THAT ISN'T FOR DEBATE.

21:59.274 --> 22:02.712
LOOK, I'VE MOVED
THE TREASURE TWICE.

22:02.799 --> 22:03.974
IT NEEDS A BIG TRUCK.

22:04.061 --> 22:05.933
NATIONAL GUARD HAS SOME
THAT WOULD WORK.

22:06.020 --> 22:07.891
I CAN GET US ONE.

22:07.978 --> 22:09.893
THIS IS GONNA BE FUN, HUH?

22:09.980 --> 22:11.330
WHO'S EXCITED? YOU?

22:11.417 --> 22:13.767
ANYONE?

22:30.174 --> 22:31.872
WHY DIDN'T YOU LEAVE?

22:31.959 --> 22:35.092
I MEAN, I KNOW
I ASKED YOU THIS BEFORE,

22:35.179 --> 22:38.661
BUT YOU HAD THE TREASURE --
WHY -- WHY STAY IN NEW YORK?

22:38.748 --> 22:40.576
YOU'VE SEEN
WHAT I HAVE HERE.

22:40.663 --> 22:42.056
WHY WOULD I GO?

22:42.143 --> 22:45.364
BECAUSE EVERYONE YOU KNOW
FOUND OUT YOU BETRAYED THEM.

22:45.451 --> 22:47.583
YOU KNOW,
THERE'S A REASON WHY

22:47.670 --> 22:50.630
OUR KIND DOESN'T STAY ANYWHERE
TOO LONG, CAFFREY.

22:50.717 --> 22:52.719
IT'S IN OUR NATURE
TO DECEIVE.

22:52.806 --> 22:54.242
YOU'VE BEEN
LIVING ON THE RUN.

22:54.329 --> 22:55.504
HOW'S THAT GOING FOR YOU?

22:57.724 --> 22:59.421
IT'S STRESSFUL.
I'M NOT GONNA LIE.

22:59.508 --> 23:01.641
YOU KNOW WHAT?

23:01.728 --> 23:03.860
WITH THIS TREASURE,
I CAN PAY OFF THE RUSSIANS.

23:03.947 --> 23:04.948
[ GRUNTS ]

23:05.035 --> 23:06.385
DISAPPEAR SOMEWHERE NICE.

23:06.472 --> 23:08.952
YOU'RE GONNA WISH
YOU NEVER HAD IT.

23:09.039 --> 23:10.737
ALL IT BRINGS IS TROUBLE.

23:10.824 --> 23:12.129
WHAT DO YOU MEAN BY THAT?

23:12.216 --> 23:14.262
THE TREASURE'S CURSED?

23:14.349 --> 23:15.742
IT'S A MONKEY'S PAW,
HUH?

23:15.829 --> 23:18.179
LOOK WHAT'S HAPPENED TO EVERYONE
WHO'S GONE AFTER IT.

23:18.266 --> 23:20.224
MAYBE YOU'RE JUST MAKING
THE WRONG KIND OF WISHES.

23:20.311 --> 23:22.966
[ VEHICLE APPROACHES ]

23:32.106 --> 23:33.324
WE'VE GOT 48 HOURS

23:33.412 --> 23:35.414
WHILE THE TRUCK'S SENT IN
FOR MAINTENANCE.

23:35.501 --> 23:38.460
I PROCURED US
SOME UNIFORMS.

23:38.547 --> 23:41.202
AW, YOU ARE GONNA LOOK ADORABLE
IN THIS, MOZZIE, HUH?

23:41.289 --> 23:43.465
IT'S A SHAME I REMOVED
THAT PRICE FROM YOUR HEAD.

23:43.552 --> 23:44.684
EH, PUT IT BACK ON.

23:44.771 --> 23:46.729
YOU'LL MAKE
A GREAT HUMAN SHIELD.

23:46.816 --> 23:48.514
TIME TO CHECK IN
WITH YOUR MISSUS.

23:50.516 --> 23:51.517
ANY UPDATE?

23:51.604 --> 23:53.301
JONES IS WORKING
AN ANGLE.

23:53.388 --> 23:54.607
IT'S A LONG SHOT,

23:54.694 --> 23:56.609
BUT EVERY HOUR WE BUY
GETS THEM CLOSER

23:56.696 --> 23:57.827
TO FINDING ELIZABETH.

23:57.914 --> 23:59.438
WE WON'T BE ABLE
TO STALL AGAIN.

23:59.525 --> 24:00.874
IF THEY DON'T
FIND HER SOON...

24:00.961 --> 24:02.658
WE'LL HAVE TO GO THROUGH
WITH THE BREAK-IN.

24:19.588 --> 24:21.068
Diana: THE SAFE HOUSE
WAS A DECOY.

24:21.155 --> 24:22.025
KELLER'S PLAYING WITH US.

24:23.331 --> 24:24.506
WHAT?

24:24.593 --> 24:25.681
CHERRY BLOSSOMS.

24:27.291 --> 24:29.250
CLEAR THE TABLE.

24:30.599 --> 24:31.818
OKAY, SO, LISTEN UP.

24:31.905 --> 24:34.037
ERTs FOUND FAINT TRACES
OF CHERRY-BLOSSOM POLLEN

24:34.124 --> 24:36.083
ON ONE OF THE SHOE PRINTS
AT THE CRIME SCENE.

24:36.170 --> 24:38.302
THE POLLEN WE FOUND WAS
OF A VARIETY CALLED FUGENZO.

24:38.389 --> 24:40.000
NOW, ACCORDING TO
PARKS AND REC,

24:40.087 --> 24:41.741
ONLY ONE PLACE
HAS THAT SPECIFIC TYPE.

24:41.828 --> 24:43.612
THERE'S A DAMN GOOD CHANCE
ELIZABETH CAN BE FOUND

24:43.699 --> 24:45.266
SOMEWHERE
IN THIS RADIUS.

24:45.353 --> 24:46.528
HIT THE STREETS.
GO DOOR-TO-DOOR.

24:46.615 --> 24:47.703
WHATEVER IT TAKES.
LET'S GO.

24:58.932 --> 24:59.933
MM.

25:14.034 --> 25:15.644
I COULD WRITE IT FOR YOU,
IF IT HELPS.

25:15.731 --> 25:16.950
DON'T TALK TO ME.
I'M FINE.

25:17.037 --> 25:18.299
IF KELLER COMES BACK LATE,

25:18.386 --> 25:20.083
YOU COULD ALWAYS LEARN
TO BE A LEFTY.

25:20.170 --> 25:21.868
AND YOU CAN LEARN
TO WALK WITH ONE FOOT.

25:21.955 --> 25:23.913
[ SIGHS ]

25:24.000 --> 25:25.567
LOOK,
IT'S NEW YORK CITY.

25:25.654 --> 25:27.613
THERE'S A PHARMACY
ON EVERY CORNER.

25:27.700 --> 25:29.179
BUT WITHOUT
ANTIBIOTICS...

25:31.921 --> 25:32.922
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

25:33.009 --> 25:34.576
DON'T MOVE.

25:34.663 --> 25:36.012
WHERE WOULD I GO?

25:39.015 --> 25:41.017
[ DOOR OPENS ]

25:42.236 --> 25:43.150
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

25:54.161 --> 25:56.032
ARE YOU OKAY?

25:56.119 --> 25:57.338
FINE.

25:57.425 --> 25:59.166
YOU KNOW, THE FIRST THING
I LEARNED

25:59.253 --> 26:00.994
ABOUT THE LIFE
OF A CON

26:01.081 --> 26:03.039
IS THAT
IN ORDER TO SURVIVE,

26:03.126 --> 26:05.389
YOU HAVE TO LOOK OUT
FOR YOURSELF.

26:05.476 --> 26:06.913
THEN WHY ARE YOU HERE?

26:07.000 --> 26:08.828
SURVIVAL IS OVERRATED.

26:08.915 --> 26:10.351
AND I FIND MYSELF
REMINDED

26:10.438 --> 26:13.920
THAT AN UNSHARED LIFE
IS NOT LIVING.

26:14.007 --> 26:15.443
SO YOU'RE SAYING
YOU CARE?

26:15.530 --> 26:17.184
ABOUT MRS. SUIT.

26:18.838 --> 26:19.926
AND...

26:27.977 --> 26:29.849
REMIND YOU
OF THE GOOD OLD DAYS, BUDDY?

26:29.936 --> 26:31.677
HMM?

26:31.764 --> 26:33.287
YOU'RE USING
ALL THE OXYGEN.

26:33.374 --> 26:34.418
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:34.505 --> 26:35.855
YOU SEE,
AFTER THAT LAST TIME,

26:35.942 --> 26:37.421
WE WERE SNEAKING OUT
OF SOMEWHERE

26:37.508 --> 26:39.423
BECAUSE YOU GOT CAUGHT IN BED
WITH THAT PRINCESS.

26:39.510 --> 26:41.817
I DIDN'T GET CAUGHT
IN BED WITH HER.

26:41.904 --> 26:44.559
THEY FOUND ME ON THE LEDGE
OUTSIDE HER WINDOW.

26:44.646 --> 26:46.605
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:46.692 --> 26:48.868
I REMEMBER SEEING YOU
STANDING THERE

26:48.955 --> 26:51.653
WITH NOTHING BUT A SOLID-GOLD
TRAY COVERING YOUR JUNK.

26:51.740 --> 26:53.742
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:53.829 --> 26:55.439
I WAS THE ONE THAT GOT YOU
DOWN FROM THERE

26:55.526 --> 26:56.876
BEFORE THEY STARTED
SHOOTING AT YOU.

26:56.963 --> 26:58.486
YEAH.

26:58.573 --> 27:00.053
YOU HAD MY BACK THEN.

27:03.143 --> 27:04.797
LIKE I SAID,
"THE GOOD OLD DAYS."

27:04.884 --> 27:05.885
THEY WERE.

27:05.972 --> 27:07.930
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU,
KELLER?

27:08.017 --> 27:10.977
I COULD ASK
THE SAME THING TO YOU, NEAL.

27:14.720 --> 27:16.417
I COULD ASK
THE SAME THING TO YOU.

27:21.509 --> 27:22.858
YOU'LL HAVE TO
TURN AROUND.

27:22.945 --> 27:24.120
THIS AREA'S OFF-LIMITS.

27:24.207 --> 27:26.383
UH, THAT'S PRECISELY
WHY WE'RE HERE.

27:26.470 --> 27:28.037
YOU GOT
THE PAPERWORK?
YEAH.

27:28.124 --> 27:29.735
HERE.

27:29.822 --> 27:31.345
YOU PUT OUT AN ORDER FOR TRUCKS,
SO WE BROUGHT YOU A TRUCK.

27:31.432 --> 27:32.694
I HAVEN'T SEEN THIS.

27:32.781 --> 27:34.391
UNTIL I SEE THIS
COME THROUGH PROPER CHANNELS,

27:34.478 --> 27:35.915
YOU'RE NOT COMING IN.

27:36.002 --> 27:38.134
YOU'RE HOLDING THE ORDERS
IN YOUR HAND RIGHT NOW.

27:38.221 --> 27:40.354
SORRY, BUDDY.
TURN THE TRUCK AROUND.

27:40.441 --> 27:41.660
FINE.

27:41.747 --> 27:44.271
THEN THIS TRUCK
IS YOUR RESPONSIBILITY.

27:46.012 --> 27:46.969
[ TRUCK DOOR CLOSES ]

27:49.842 --> 27:51.321
GIVE ME THE PLANS.

27:52.975 --> 27:54.455
WHY?GIVE ME THE PLANS.

27:57.632 --> 27:59.373
Peter:
YOU SEE THIS "X"?

27:59.460 --> 28:02.985
THIS TRUCK NEEDS TO BE PARKED
RIGHT ON IT.

28:03.072 --> 28:05.161
[ PETER SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
IN DISTANCE ]

28:05.248 --> 28:06.902
IS BURKE SHOWING THAT COP
OUR PLAN?

28:06.989 --> 28:08.338
LOOK, I'M SURE HE'S GOT IT
UNDER CONTROL.

28:08.425 --> 28:10.819
Peter: THE TRUCK NOW
IS YOUR PROBLEM.

28:10.906 --> 28:12.821
HE'S CRAZY.
I RESPECT THAT.

28:12.908 --> 28:13.648
YES, IT IS.

28:13.735 --> 28:15.084
THIS "X."

28:15.171 --> 28:18.566
PARK THE TRUCK ON IT NOW.

28:18.653 --> 28:20.916
AND WHAT IF I DON'T?

28:21.003 --> 28:24.964
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

28:25.051 --> 28:27.488
OH, IT'S YOUR ASS,
NOT OURS.

28:29.403 --> 28:31.492
THANKS FOR YOUR HELP.

28:33.015 --> 28:34.451
OKAY, SO NOW

28:34.538 --> 28:36.627
THEY'VE GOT OUR TRUCK
AND OUR PLANS TO BREAK IN?

28:36.715 --> 28:37.977
YEAH.

28:38.064 --> 28:39.543
WHAT HAPPENS
IF THEY DON'T DRIVE IT IN?

28:39.630 --> 28:40.675
THEY WILL.

28:40.762 --> 28:42.808
Come on.
Drive it in.

28:42.895 --> 28:44.723
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

28:44.810 --> 28:46.376
NICELY PLAYED, SUIT.

28:46.463 --> 28:48.857
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GET
TO THE RENDEZVOUS POINT.

28:53.601 --> 28:55.472
ALL RIGHT,
WE MUST BE THERE.

28:55.559 --> 28:57.605
THE TRUCK HASN'T MOVED
IN A WHILE.

28:57.692 --> 29:00.869
IT'S FIVE AFTER.
EVERYONE SHOULD BE AT LUNCH.

29:00.956 --> 29:02.697
ALL RIGHT. WE GOT 55 MINUTES
TO LOAD EVERYTHING UP.

29:02.784 --> 29:03.698
YEP.

29:15.841 --> 29:17.712
[ SIGHS ]

29:17.799 --> 29:19.148
WHAT IS IT?

29:19.235 --> 29:21.977
APPARENTLY,
THEY SKIPPED LUNCH.

29:32.771 --> 29:34.903
WE HAVE PLAINCLOTHES
SEARCHING THE RADIUS, BOSS,

29:34.990 --> 29:37.166
WE HAVE CELL PHONE INTERCEPTORS
PICKING UP ALL NEARBY CALLS,

29:37.253 --> 29:39.125
AND WE HAVE AGENTS ON THE ROOFS,
SCANNING THE CROWD.

29:39.212 --> 29:40.256
GOOD WORK, DIANA.JONES: Let me talk to him.

29:40.343 --> 29:41.649
PETER.

29:41.736 --> 29:43.216
THAT STORAGE FACILITY
YOU HAD ME LOOKING INTO?

29:43.303 --> 29:44.783
Yeah?

29:44.870 --> 29:46.959
Whatever they found there,
it's important enough

29:47.046 --> 29:49.048
that they have the 22nd Precinct
doing double shifts.

29:49.135 --> 29:50.440
THAT MEAN
WORKING THROUGH LUNCH?

29:50.527 --> 29:51.833
I GUESS SO.

29:51.920 --> 29:54.140
JONES,
WE NEED TO FIND HER NOW.

29:54.227 --> 29:55.489
EVERY SECOND COUNTS.

29:55.576 --> 29:57.056
[ CELL PHONE BEEPS ]

29:57.143 --> 29:58.535
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

29:58.622 --> 30:00.407
Neal:
WE GOT A PROBLEM.

30:00.494 --> 30:03.889
THIS IS SOME KIND OF
DOUBLE-CROSS.

30:03.976 --> 30:07.501
NOT EVERYTHING
IS AN ANGLE, KELLER.

30:07.588 --> 30:08.850
WE SHOULD'VE BROUGHT GUNS.

30:08.937 --> 30:10.243
YEAH, 'CAUSE THAT WOULD'VE
WORKED OUT WELL.

30:16.989 --> 30:18.425
JUST LIKE OLD TIMES.

30:18.512 --> 30:19.426
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:19.513 --> 30:21.863
Neal:
EXCUSE ME.

30:21.950 --> 30:23.647
ARE YOU
THE SERGEANT IN CHARGE?

30:23.734 --> 30:24.866
I AM.

30:24.953 --> 30:26.346
GOOD. GLAD YOU GUYS
COULD MAKE IT.

30:26.433 --> 30:28.870
LOOK, WE GOT TO LOAD
CONTAINER 10 INTO THE TRUCK.

30:28.957 --> 30:30.306
WELL, OUR ORDERS ARE

30:30.393 --> 30:32.439
TO WAIT FOR THE WARRANT
TO COME IN FOR CONTAINER 2.

30:34.006 --> 30:35.398
YOU'RE 22nd PRECINCT,
RIGHT?

30:35.485 --> 30:36.878
THAT'S US.

30:36.965 --> 30:38.749
THEN YOU'RE HERE TO HELP US
LOAD CONTAINER 10.

30:38.837 --> 30:40.316
NO, WE WERE TOLD
THAT THE WARRANT FOR THAT

30:40.403 --> 30:41.709
WOULDN'T BE IN
TILL THE END OF THE DAY.

30:41.796 --> 30:43.058
NAH, IT CAME THROUGH
20 MINUTES AGO.

30:43.145 --> 30:44.494
COME ON. WE'LL SHOW YOU.
WE ALREADY BEEN THERE.

30:44.581 --> 30:46.975
NOW, LOOK, THERE'S 17 WOOD BOXES
THAT NEED TO BE HAULED OUT.

30:47.062 --> 30:48.803
YEAH, MAKES YOU WONDER
WHAT'S INSIDE THEM, RIGHT?

30:48.890 --> 30:49.891
YEAH, DON'T IT?

30:49.978 --> 30:51.327
BUT I GOT TOLD
IF I LOOKED,

30:51.414 --> 30:52.894
I'D BE WORKING DISPATCH
FOR A YEAR.

30:52.981 --> 30:53.939
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:54.026 --> 30:55.375
ARE YOU SURE
THIS IS RIGHT?

30:55.462 --> 30:57.203
IF NOT, THEN WHY
WOULD I HAVE THE KEY?
YEAH.

30:59.727 --> 31:02.512
A BUNCH OF NEO-NAZIS?
ABOVE MY PAY GRADE.

31:02.599 --> 31:04.950
HOW MANY BOXES
DOES THAT LOOK LIKE, HUH?

31:05.037 --> 31:06.647
IT LOOKS LIKE 17 TO ME.

31:08.431 --> 31:10.303
EVERYBODY,
CHANGE OF PLANS!

31:10.390 --> 31:12.609
WE'RE EMPTYING
THIS CONTAINER OUT.

31:12.696 --> 31:14.002
ALL RIGHT,
THEY'RE ALL YOURS.

31:15.917 --> 31:17.527
BUT I NEED TO SEE
THE WARRANT, OF COURSE.

31:17.614 --> 31:19.573
OF COURSE. WE'LL GET THEM
TO YOU IN A BIT.

31:19.660 --> 31:22.837
I GOT TO SEE IT NOW.
YOU KNOW, PROCEDURES AND ALL.

31:24.795 --> 31:26.710
SURE.

31:26.797 --> 31:29.713
COME WITH ME.

31:29.800 --> 31:32.325
HEAVIEST TO THE BACK,
IF YOU CAN.

31:34.414 --> 31:35.719
I HOPE YOU UNDERSTAND,

31:35.806 --> 31:37.504
BUT THINGS JUST HAVE TO
BE DONE A CERTAIN WAY.

31:37.591 --> 31:39.027
YEAH, RULES ARE RULES.
I GET IT.

31:40.855 --> 31:42.770
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

31:42.857 --> 31:43.858
Neal:
SERGEANT!

31:43.945 --> 31:45.599
NO, NO,
IT'S NO TROUBLE AT ALL.

31:45.686 --> 31:46.774
HE'S RIGHT HERE, SIR.

31:46.861 --> 31:48.863
IT'S THE D.A.'s OFFICE.

31:48.950 --> 31:51.910
THEY WANT TO
TOUCH BASE WITH YOU.

31:51.997 --> 31:53.433
SERGEANT BRUBAKER.

31:53.520 --> 31:55.957
PETER: Sergeant, this is
the District Attorney's aide.

31:56.044 --> 31:58.046
HOW CAN I HELP
CLEAR THINGS UP?

31:58.133 --> 32:00.744
WHAT PART OF "NO KILLING"
DO YOU KEEP FORGETTING?

32:00.831 --> 32:02.877
FINDING A DEAD BODY
CAN TAKE HOURS.

32:02.964 --> 32:04.835
THIS LIE CAN FALL APART
ANY SECOND.

32:04.923 --> 32:06.620
PETER
WILL TAKE CARE OF IT.

32:06.707 --> 32:08.752
YOU REALLY HAVE GONE NATIVE,
HAVEN'T YOU?

32:08.839 --> 32:10.667
Sgt. Brubaker: GOT IT.[ CELL PHONE BEEPS ]

32:10.754 --> 32:13.801
IT'S ALL GOOD, GENTS.
THANK YOU.

32:13.888 --> 32:15.498
THANK YOU, SIR.
TAKE IT EASY.

32:17.109 --> 32:18.719
NO, YOU WALK
IN FRONT OF ME.

32:20.155 --> 32:22.157
WE GOT A HIT
ON THE ACCOMPLICE'S ACCOUNT.

32:22.244 --> 32:24.290
IT WAS USED AT A PHARMACY
THREE BLOCKS AWAY --

32:24.377 --> 32:26.466
RUBBING ALCOHOL,
ANTIBACTERIALS, AND BANDAGES.

32:26.553 --> 32:28.598
SOUNDS LIKE A GUY
WORRIED ABOUT A DOG BITE.

32:28.685 --> 32:30.557
EVERYBODY SPREAD OUT.
HE'S IN THE VICINITY.

32:30.644 --> 32:32.472
ALL RIGHT.
THANKS A LOT, GUYS.

32:32.559 --> 32:33.690
APPRECIATE THE HELP.

32:33.777 --> 32:35.736
HEY, THE BEERS ARE ON ME,
RIGHT?

32:38.478 --> 32:39.566
YOU READY?

32:39.653 --> 32:41.220
YEP.
I THINK WE'RE GOOD TO --

32:41.307 --> 32:42.612
OH!

32:44.179 --> 32:45.528
[ SMOOCHES ]

32:45.615 --> 32:47.052
THANKS, HON.

32:47.139 --> 32:48.314
ALL RIGHT,
HERE'S FOR NOTHING.

33:05.113 --> 33:06.245
OKAY, I DON'T KNOW

33:06.332 --> 33:08.029
HOW THE HELL
YOU GOT OUT OF THERE, BUT --

33:08.116 --> 33:09.030
AAAAAAAH!

33:09.117 --> 33:10.031
MY HAND!

33:10.118 --> 33:11.990
[ GUNSHOT ]

33:12.077 --> 33:13.165
GO AHEAD.

33:13.252 --> 33:15.602
Jones: DROP IT.

33:18.039 --> 33:21.608
NEAL'S NOT PICKING UP.
I THINK SOMETHING WENT WRONG.

33:21.695 --> 33:22.957
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

33:23.044 --> 33:24.002
NEAL?

33:24.089 --> 33:25.612
DISAPPOINTED?

33:25.699 --> 33:26.700
EL.

33:26.787 --> 33:27.570
SHE'S OKAY?

33:27.657 --> 33:28.745
I'm safe.

33:28.832 --> 33:30.399
OH, THANK GOD.

33:30.486 --> 33:31.618
They caught
the guy holding me.

33:31.705 --> 33:32.706
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

33:32.793 --> 33:34.664
I AM NOW.
WHERE ARE YOU?

33:34.751 --> 33:37.319
Uh, 23rd and 3rd.
They're taking me home.

33:37.406 --> 33:38.494
WHERE'S KELLER?

33:38.581 --> 33:39.756
HE'S WITH NEAL.

33:39.843 --> 33:41.497
I CAN'T GET AHOLD OF HIM.

33:41.584 --> 33:42.759
GO GET HIM.

33:42.846 --> 33:43.891
El.

33:43.978 --> 33:46.328
GO.
THEN COME BACK TO ME.

33:46.415 --> 33:48.417
[ SIGHS ][ CELL PHONE BEEPS ]

33:48.504 --> 33:50.637
MOZZIE, WE NEED TO FIGURE OUT
WHERE KELLER'S HEADED.

33:50.724 --> 33:52.421
OH, WAY AHEAD OF YOU,
SUIT.

33:52.508 --> 33:55.163
I'VE ALREADY MAPPED OUT
POTENTIAL ESCAPE ROUTES.

33:55.250 --> 33:57.557
FROM THIS POINT,
IT'S 2.4 MILES TO THE DOCKS

33:57.644 --> 33:58.906
AND 16.1 TO TETERBORO.

33:58.993 --> 34:01.126
ALL RIGHT. YOU TAKE THE AIR,
I'LL TAKE THE SEA,

34:01.213 --> 34:02.997
AND THE BUREAU
WILL BACK US UP ON BOTH.

34:04.564 --> 34:06.479
I'M GONNA NEED TO
GET IN ONE OF THESE CARS.

34:06.566 --> 34:07.958
OH, ALREADY DONE.

34:20.449 --> 34:22.408
[ GROANS ]

34:33.462 --> 34:34.855
All right.

34:36.161 --> 34:38.032
[ GRUNTING ]

34:47.259 --> 34:48.173
YOU'VE GOT TO BE
KIDDING ME.

34:51.001 --> 34:52.568
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

35:10.673 --> 35:12.632
CAFFREY.

35:12.719 --> 35:14.199
COME ON, CAFFREY.
I KNOW YOU'RE IN THERE.

35:15.983 --> 35:18.333
THERE'S NO WAY OUT,
BUDDY.

35:18.420 --> 35:19.465
[ GUNSHOT ]

35:27.212 --> 35:30.389
YOU AND ME...
TO THE BITTER END, EH?

35:45.273 --> 35:46.274
ALL RIGHT.

36:03.552 --> 36:05.598
NOT A RAPHAEL.

36:05.685 --> 36:07.991
YOU WOULDN'T.

36:14.563 --> 36:16.130
[ Groaning ]
OH, GOD.

36:17.871 --> 36:19.873
FIRST RULE OF A FIGHT --

36:19.960 --> 36:22.441
ALWAYS GO
FOR THE WEAK SPOT.

36:31.711 --> 36:33.930
EASY THERE, BURKE,
HUH?

36:34.017 --> 36:35.889
I GOT THE WIFE.
REMEMBER THAT.

36:35.976 --> 36:36.977
NOT ANYMORE.

36:37.064 --> 36:37.978
HUH?

36:40.937 --> 36:43.113
"NOT ANYMORE"?
WHAT ARE YOU, BLUFFING ME?

36:43.201 --> 36:44.376
CALL YOUR GUY.

36:44.463 --> 36:45.855
TELL HIM HE CAN GET
A GREAT SLICE OF PIZZA

36:45.942 --> 36:47.596
RIGHT AT THE CORNER
OF 23rd AND 3rd.

36:47.683 --> 36:49.119
DON'T MATTER...

36:49.207 --> 36:51.774
'CAUSE I'LL GET HER AGAIN.

36:51.861 --> 36:53.559
AND AGAIN AND AGAIN.

37:08.574 --> 37:09.705
HEY. HEY!

37:13.927 --> 37:14.841
COME ON.

37:20.847 --> 37:21.935
[ GUNSHOT ]

37:22.022 --> 37:22.892
UNH!

37:26.069 --> 37:28.681
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

37:30.160 --> 37:32.250
[ GROANS ]

37:32.337 --> 37:33.860
DID WE REALLY
GET ELIZABETH?

37:33.947 --> 37:35.122
WE DID.

37:35.209 --> 37:38.256
HOW'D YOU MAKE
THAT SHOT?

37:38.343 --> 37:40.345
LONG STORY.

37:46.873 --> 37:50.920
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

37:57.449 --> 37:59.712
[ DOOR OPENS ]

37:59.799 --> 38:01.583
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

38:06.806 --> 38:07.937
YOU OKAY?

38:08.024 --> 38:08.938
YEAH. YOU?

38:09.025 --> 38:11.941
WHAT NOW?

38:12.028 --> 38:13.334
KELLER NEEDS TO
GO AWAY FOREVER,

38:13.421 --> 38:14.379
AND TO MAKE THAT HAPPEN,

38:14.466 --> 38:15.815
I NEED TO GIVE
A FULL CONFESSION.

38:15.902 --> 38:17.599
THAT MEANS PRISON.

38:17.686 --> 38:18.905
A LOT OF IT.

38:18.992 --> 38:20.298
I KNOW.

38:20.385 --> 38:23.170
I'LL TURN MYSELF IN
TOMORROW MORNING.

38:23.257 --> 38:26.695
THAT SHOULD GIVE YOU
A 12-HOUR HEAD START.

38:26.782 --> 38:28.306
THE TREASURE'S GONE.

38:28.393 --> 38:31.265
DO YOU THINK
YOU CAN SURVIVE WITHOUT IT?

38:31.352 --> 38:34.442
I ALWAYS HAVE
A CONTINGENCY PLAN.

38:34.529 --> 38:36.618
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:36.705 --> 38:38.272
IF YOU WANT
A HAPPY ENDING,

38:38.359 --> 38:40.187
IT DEPENDS ON
WHERE YOU STOP THE STORY.

38:40.274 --> 38:41.623
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:41.710 --> 38:43.321
I THINK OUR STORY
STOPS HERE.

38:45.235 --> 38:47.934
AND...ENDS WELL.

38:49.718 --> 38:51.981
TILL THE NEXT CHAPTER.

38:52.068 --> 38:55.245
TILL THE NEXT CHAPTER.

39:24.100 --> 39:25.798
GOOD MORNING, NEAL.

39:25.885 --> 39:26.973
MORNING.

39:28.844 --> 39:30.150
HOW'S ELIZABETH?

39:30.237 --> 39:32.587
SHE'S WELL,
CONSIDERING.

39:32.674 --> 39:33.936
I KNOW WHAT I'VE DONE.

39:35.982 --> 39:37.853
AND I KNOW WHAT I NEED TO DO
TO TAKE KELLER DOWN.

39:37.940 --> 39:40.682
I'M READY TO MAKE
A FULL CONFESSION.

39:40.769 --> 39:43.816
YOU KNOW
WHAT THAT WILL MEAN.

39:43.903 --> 39:45.121
I DO.

39:45.208 --> 39:47.689
ARE YOU SURE?

39:47.776 --> 39:49.169
YOU'RE WILLING TO GIVE UP
EVERYTHING?

39:50.736 --> 39:51.824
YEAH.

39:54.348 --> 39:57.264
I'M GLAD TO HEAR THAT.

39:57.351 --> 39:59.962
BUT BEFORE YOU GO ANY FURTHER,
I WANT TO SHOW YOU SOMETHING.

40:00.049 --> 40:01.007
PETER, PLEASE.

40:01.094 --> 40:02.661
I NEED TO
GET THIS OUT NOW.

40:02.748 --> 40:04.314
WATCH.

40:06.273 --> 40:07.666
WHAT IS THIS?

40:07.753 --> 40:11.452
KELLER'S INTERROGATION
FROM LAST NIGHT.

40:11.539 --> 40:12.497
I STOLE THE TREASURE.

40:12.584 --> 40:14.107
Interpreter: [ SPEAKING RUSSIAN ]

40:14.194 --> 40:16.239
AND I WAS THE ONE THAT BURNED DOWN THE WAREHOUSE

40:16.326 --> 40:17.632
AND TOOK IT
FROM VINCENT ADLER.

40:17.719 --> 40:18.981
[ SPEAKING RUSSIAN ]

40:19.068 --> 40:20.635
ADLER DIDN'T DESERVE IT.

40:20.722 --> 40:23.029
IT BELONGS TO
THE PEOPLE OF RUSSIA.

40:23.116 --> 40:25.945
I TAKE
FULL RESPONSIBILITY.

40:26.032 --> 40:29.818
I ALONE RECOVERED
THIS PRICELESS ARTWORK...

40:29.905 --> 40:31.124
[ SPEAKING RUSSIAN ]

40:31.211 --> 40:33.126
...THAT WAS SO NEARLY LOST
TO HISTORY.

40:33.213 --> 40:35.084
[ REMOTE CLICKS,
VIDEO STOPS ]

40:35.171 --> 40:37.086
HE TOOK CREDIT FOR IT.

40:37.173 --> 40:39.349
YEP.

40:39.437 --> 40:40.699
WHY?

40:40.786 --> 40:42.962
HE SAID HE'D GIVE
A FULL CONFESSION

40:43.049 --> 40:46.095
AS LONG AS IT WAS IN FRONT OF
THE RUSSIAN AUTHORITIES.

40:46.182 --> 40:47.488
THE TREASURE
WAS ORIGINALLY PILLAGED

40:47.575 --> 40:48.881
FROM THE RUSSIAN MUSEUMS.

40:48.968 --> 40:51.710
AND NOW KELLER CLAIMED
THAT HE STOLE IT TO SAVE IT,

40:51.797 --> 40:53.494
RETURN IT
TO THE MOTHERLAND.

40:53.581 --> 40:55.714
THE RUSSIAN MOB
WANTED HIM DEAD.

40:55.801 --> 40:58.412
YEAH, AND NOW THEY'RE HELPING
PAY FOR HIS LEGAL DEFENSE.

40:58.499 --> 40:59.631
SON OF A BITCH.

40:59.718 --> 41:01.676
AS FAR AS ANYONE
IS CONCERNED,

41:01.763 --> 41:05.593
HE'S THE ONE WHO RECOVERED
THE TREASURE OF A LIFETIME.

41:05.680 --> 41:09.205
NOT YOU.
NOT MOZZIE.

41:09.292 --> 41:10.468
THAT BOTHER YOU?

41:12.513 --> 41:13.601
NO.

41:16.169 --> 41:17.126
IT DOESN'T.

41:18.519 --> 41:21.870
I KNOW WHAT YOU WERE
PREPARED TO DO.

41:21.957 --> 41:25.308
AND IT MEANS A LOT
THAT YOU WERE WILLING TO DO IT.

41:25.395 --> 41:26.919
WHAT HAPPENS NOW?

41:27.006 --> 41:29.182
Diana: PETER.

41:29.269 --> 41:30.836
YOU'RE GONNA WANT
TO SEE THIS.

41:30.923 --> 41:31.924
DIANA.
TRUST ME.

41:46.373 --> 41:50.377
WHAT IS IT?

41:50.464 --> 41:53.423
THIS IS A LETTER
FROM THE U.S. PROBATION OFFICE.

41:53.511 --> 41:56.426
IT IS TO INFORM YOU THAT
A HEARING HAS BEEN SCHEDULED

41:56.514 --> 41:58.124
CONCERNING YOUR PROBATION.

41:58.211 --> 42:00.561
BECAUSE OF YOUR
OUTSTANDING SERVICE,

42:00.648 --> 42:02.911
INCLUDING RECOVERING
THE TREASURE

42:02.998 --> 42:04.434
AND CATCHING KELLER,

42:04.522 --> 42:07.742
THE U.S. PROBATION OFFICE
IS CONVENING A HEARING

42:07.829 --> 42:10.571
TO DISCUSS THE COMMUTATION
OF YOUR SENTENCE.

42:10.658 --> 42:12.921
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

42:13.008 --> 42:16.229
IT MEANS NO ANKLET.

42:16.316 --> 42:18.623
NO NOTHING.

42:18.710 --> 42:20.625
IN THREE MONTHS,
YOU COULD BE A FREE MAN.
